---
import BaseLayout from '../../layouts/BaseLayout.astro';
---

<BaseLayout
  title="Privacy Policy | LaTech Editorial Publishing"
  description="How we collect, use, and protect your information when you visit our site or contact us."
>
  <div class="page-header">
    <div class="container">
      <h1>Privacy Policy</h1>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="page-content">
    <div class="narrow-content">
      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Overview</h2>
        <p>
          We respect your privacy and collect minimal data. This privacy policy explains what information we collect, how we use it, and how we protect it. This is a static website hosted on GitHub Pages, and we do not use cookies for tracking purposes.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Data We Collect</h2>
        <h3>Website Usage</h3>
        <p>
          This is a static website, which means:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>We do not collect personal information automatically</li>
          <li>We do not use cookies for tracking</li>
          <li>We do not use analytics tools that collect personal data (currently)</li>
        </ul>
        
        <h3>Contact Form</h3>
        <p>
          If you use our contact form, your submission is processed by Formspree (a third-party service). Formspree collects:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Name</li>
          <li>Email address</li>
          <li>Subject</li>
          <li>Message content</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          This information is used solely to respond to your inquiry. Please review <a href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Formspree's privacy policy</a> for details on how they handle your data.
        </p>
        
        <h3>Future Analytics</h3>
        <p>
          We may add privacy-respecting analytics tools in the future. If we do, we will update this policy and use tools that minimize data collection and respect user privacy (such as Plausible or Fathom Analytics).
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>How Data Is Used</h2>
        <p>
          Any data we collect is used only for the following purposes:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Contact form submissions:</strong> To respond to your inquiries and communicate with you</li>
          <li><strong>No data is sold or shared:</strong> We do not sell, rent, or share your personal information with third parties for marketing purposes</li>
          <li><strong>No tracking:</strong> We do not track your browsing behavior or use personal data for advertising</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Third Parties</h2>
        <p>
          We use the following third-party services:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>GitHub Pages:</strong> Our website is hosted on GitHub Pages. Please review <a href="https://docs.github.com/en/site-policy/privacy-policies/github-privacy-statement" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">GitHub's privacy policy</a> for information about their data practices.</li>
          <li><strong>Formspree:</strong> Contact form submissions are processed by Formspree. See their <a href="https://formspree.io/legal/privacy-policy" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">privacy policy</a> for details.</li>
        </ul>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Your Rights</h2>
        <p>
          You have the right to:
        </p>
        <ul>
          <li>Request information about what data we have collected about you</li>
          <li>Request deletion of your data</li>
          <li>Opt out of any future data collection (where applicable)</li>
        </ul>
        <p>
          To exercise these rights, please <a href="/contact/">contact us</a>.
        </p>
      </section>

      <section class="content-section">
        <h2>Updates to Policy</h2>
        <p>
          We may update this privacy policy from time to time. When we make changes, we will update the "Last updated" date below. Significant changes will be announced on our website.
        </p>
        <p class="last-updated">
          <strong>Last updated:</strong> January 2024
        </p>
      </section>
    </div>
  </div>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
  .page-header {
    background-color: var(--color-primary);
    color: var(--color-white);
    padding: var(--spacing-2xl) 0;
    text-align: center;
  }
  
  .page-header h1 {
    color: var(--color-white);
    margin-bottom: 0;
  }
  
  .page-content {
    padding: var(--spacing-2xl) 0;
  }
  
  .content-section {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-xl);
  }
  
  .content-section h2 {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-md);
    font-size: 1.75rem;
  }
  
  .content-section h3 {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
    font-size: 1.25rem;
  }
  
  .content-section ul {
    margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
  }
  
  .content-section li {
    margin-bottom: var(--spacing-sm);
  }
  
  .last-updated {
    font-size: 0.875rem;
    color: var(--color-text-light);
    font-style: italic;
    margin-top: var(--spacing-md);
  }
</style>
